  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0da7 \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dd4 \u0dad\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dda \u0db8\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0d87\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd6  \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd3\u0dba \u0db0\u0dd3\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca 06\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "06 Indian fishermen caught fish in the coast of this country",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Navy says that 06 Indian fishermen were arrested yesterday (20th) along with an Indian trawler who was fishing illegally in the coast north of Mannar.",
        "The Indian fishermen were arrested by a group of officers belonging to the Northern Naval Command while they were fishing in the northern coast of Mannar.",
        "The Navy took steps to take the Indian fishermen along with the fishing vessel along with the fish they caught and the fishing gear to Thalaimannar and hand them over to the Fisheries Inspectorate.",
        "Meanwhile, the Navy added that 29 Indian fishermen along with 4 Indian trawlers have been arrested by the Navy in the month of July alone and legal action has been taken."
      ],
